strace as a powerful diagnostic, instructional, and debugging tool for Linux. It allows you to intercept and record the system calls made by a process and the signals it receives.

The Professional Definition
"strace is a userspace utility that monitors the interaction between a process and the Linux kernel. Since every meaningful action a program takes—such as reading a file, opening a network socket, or allocating memory—requires a system call, strace provides a transparent window into exactly what a binary is doing in real-time, even without access to the source code."

